snippet: Whether Eugene Palmer, who the police say fatally shot his daughter-in-law, could have survived for a year in Harriman State Park in New York is debated.
abstract: Police in Haverstraw, NY, are still searching for Eugene Palmer, 73-year-old retired truck driver who shot and killed his daughter-in-law Tammy Palmer and vanished into woods of Harriman State Park in fall of 2012; question remains whether Palmer, who suffered from diabetes and heart ailments, is hardy enough to have survived in wilderness for year.
lead_paragraph: Whether Eugene Palmer, who the police say fatally shot his daughter-in-law, could have survived for a year in Harriman State Park in New York is debated.

headline.main: Into These Woods, Suspect in a Killing Vanished a Year Ago
